{"article_id":"h8nrHx4p7cKkxt18","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"On Thursday , Education Secretary Betsy DeVos announced","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that she would be essentially gutting Obama-era Title IX sexual assault protections .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Implemented in 2011 during President Obama 's term ,","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"the protections and guidelines were lauded by advocates and sexual assault survivors as a step forward .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"But these guidelines have been controversial from the start","depth":3},{"id":5,"text":"with critics saying","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"that they infringe on the rights of those accused of sexual assault .","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"If you vehemently disagree with DeVos ' decision ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"here 's how to argue about Title IX .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"In her announcement , DeVos said","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that the 2011 Title IX guidelines were insufficient and overreaching ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"and contributed to a `` failed system . ''","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"She added :","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"`` Instead of working with schools on behalf of students ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"the prior administration weaponized the Office for Civil Rights","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"to work against schools and against students . ''","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"Though still vague in terms of what specific policy changes would be made ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"DeVos ' decision came as no surprised","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"given that the education secretary has made considerable efforts","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to recognize those accused of sexual assault publicly .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"`` Every survivor of sexual misconduct must be taken seriously .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Every student","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"accused of sexual misconduct","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"must know","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"that guilt is not predetermined .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"These are non-negotiable principles , ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"she said in her speech .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Many disagree","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"that the burden of proof should fall on sexual assault survivors .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"If you ever find yourself in an argument","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"about why DeVos ' decision is harmful for survivors ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"here are some points","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"to use .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Argument :","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Obama 's 2011 Guidelines Did n't Respect The Rights Of The Accused","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Your response :","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"In the years","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"following the implementation of the Title IX guidelines ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"those","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"accused of sexually assaulting a classmate","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"began suing their respective universities","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"for `` railroading '' them .","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"Those lawsuit plaintiffs ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"who were young men ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"that college administrators ' investigations lacked due process .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"They also maintained","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that they were innocent of sexual assault","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"and had engaged in a consensual encounter .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Sexual assault allegations are notoriously difficult to prove .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Even if there is direct evidence","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"( bodily fluids or fibers )","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"that a sexual encounter did occur ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that alone is not enough","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"to prove sexual assault .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Essentially , cases can become the alleged assailant 's word agains the alleged victim 's word .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Assuming that those involved are being truthful ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"it 's one person 's perception against another .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Studies suggest","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"that young men 's account of sexual encounters might not be the most reliable voice in the room","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"- and that they may maintain innocence","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"even after they 've been found to have assaulted a classmate .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"NIH-backed research shows","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"that men often over-interpret actions ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"thinking","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"another 's actions are more sexually charged","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"than they are actually intend to be by the other .","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"This means that some men could believe","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"that their partners are giving consent or expressing interest in a nonverbal way ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"when that may not be the case .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"Furthermore , a small , more recent survey by a journalist shows","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that some men are reluctant to ask for consent ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"seeing the question as a buzz-kill .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"Therefore , a young man","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"who is found guilty of sexual assault","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"and maintains his innocence","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"is not necessarily an indication of an unfair system ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"but more likely an indication of a culture of male entitlement .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Nonetheless , he as an accused person should be listened to","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"- he 's entitled to it by the Constitution .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Argument :","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"DeVos Was Right","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"To Say","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"There Should Be A Notice-And-Comment Period","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"Your response :","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"DeVos said","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"that guidelines will be changed","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"to include a `` notice-and-comment '' period .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"She did n't elaborate","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"on what exactly that might mean ,","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"but","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"if it means","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"she 's going to encourage universities to allow those accused to confront or cross-examine their alleged victims ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that could be devastating for true victims .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Such a process could even discourage victims from reporting sexual assaults ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"according to Annie Clark , a sexual assault survivor-turned-activist .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"`` If a survivor is told that they would have to face their rapist ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"and that person would be allowed to interrogate them ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"that could absolutely have a chilling effect , ''","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Clark told NPR .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"So","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"while the accused certainly has a right","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"to be heard ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"and investigations should be conducted in an orderly and thorough fashion ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"making victims face their alleged assailants would be incredibly cruel ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"and hurt schools ' efforts","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"to combat sexual assault on campus , overall .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Argument :","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"Obama 's Guidelines Lowered The Standard For Proof Of Guilt Too Much - And Unfairly .","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"Your response :","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"Devos was especially critical of Obama 's decision","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"to require schools use the standard of a \" preponderance of the evidence \"","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"to find the accused guilty ,","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"rather than the \" beyond a reasonable doubt \" standard","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"used by the criminal justice system .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"However ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"according to the advocacy group SurvJustice ,","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"the legal system 's standard is unnecessary","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"since college investigations do n't result in jail time , but usually at most expulsion .","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"\" That ' s not really appropriate on the campus level , ''","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"Laura Dunn , the founder and executive director of SurvJustice , told The Washington Post .","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"`` We ' re not locking people up ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"executing them ,","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"putting them away for years","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"denying their liberty . \"","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"since ,","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"as discussed above ,","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"it 's incredibly difficult to prove sexual assault `` beyond a reasonable doubt '' in most cases ,","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"using the criminal justice system 's standard could result in guilty assailants walking free .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Argument :","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"The Courts Should Handle Sexual Assault Cases , Not Schools","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"Your response :","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"According to the advocacy group Know Your IX ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"having the criminal justice system would make sexual assault investigations slower and more painful for the victims .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"When schools successfully investigate cases ,","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"they can provide accommodations for the supposed victims","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"- academic considerations , housing changes , etc . -","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"far more quickly","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"than the criminal justice system could .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"Furthermore ,","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"if and when a criminal case is brought against an alleged assailant ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"the defendant in the case and trial will be the state , not the victim ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"which could mean his or her needs are n't considered as much","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"as they should be .","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"Argument :","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"Obama 's Guidelines Made The Office Of Civil Rights ' Enforcements Unnecessarily Political","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Your response :","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"DeVos argued","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"that Obama 's policies encouraged the Department of Education 's Office of Civil Rights to push universities to punish those accused , rightly or wrongly .","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"However ,","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"according to Catherine Lhamon , the head of DOE 's Office of Civil Rights during Obama 's presidency ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"schools were not pushed to side with accusers or the accused ,","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"but to conduct investigations fairly .","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"\" Over and over again , OCR found schools","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"that were doing things","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"that were not right .","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"We called it","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"when it harmed student survivors ,","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"and we called it","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"when it harmed students","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"who were accused , \"","depth":16},{"id":162,"text":"Lhamon told The Washington Post .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"DeVos has not directly addressed Lhamon 's account ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"but instead has relied upon the criticisms of discontented university administrators and faculty members .","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"Argument :","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"DeVos 's Roll Back Of Title IX Protections Is n't About Civil Rights .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"It 's About Fairness .","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"Your response :","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"For those","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"hearing this argument ,","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"DeVos touting fairness may be appealing .","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"However ,","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"when taken in a larger context of the hollow rhetoric","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"used by the Trump administration ,","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"it 's hard not to see it as an infringement on survivors ' rights .","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"According to the Constitution 's Fourteenth Amendment ,","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"Americans have the right","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"to be free of sex-based discrimination .","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"Nonetheless , in his first 100 days in office , Trump decided to make the lot of women even more difficult","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"- a key example of how Trump disregards the needs and rights of those marginalized by American society .","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"According to the Center for American Progress ,","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"he undid the Fair Pay and Safe Workplaces Executive Order ,","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"proposed defunding Planned Parenthood ,","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"brought back the Global Gag Rule , among other things .","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"For Trump and DeVos , `` fairness '' seems not to fully take into account the situation of those harmed .","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"They strive to make sure","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"that survivor and assailant , or men and women , are treated no different by the law .","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"This would be fine","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"if we lived in an ideal world","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"free of patriarchal oppression ,","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"but unfortunately , both survivors and women need protection from societal ills and sex-based discrimination .","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"For survivors of sexual assault , DeVos ' idea of `` fairness ''","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"in dealing with Title IX","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"is not particularly fair at all .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":389,"left":201,"right":388,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":198,"right":200,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":196,"right":197,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":197,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":200,"left":4,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":388,"left":273,"right":387,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":273,"left":222,"right":272,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":220,"right":221,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":202,"right":219,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":202,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":208,"right":218,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":204,"right":207,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":9,"right":203,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":203,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":12,"right":206,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":13,"right":205,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":205,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":2